WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:05.483
Checking an entry means understanding whether the available evidence supports it.

2
00:00:06.995 --> 00:00:12.355
Vera starts from the sampled journal row and searches the documents provided and any

3
00:00:12.355 --> 00:00:14.333
authorized archives or exports.

4
00:00:15.844 --> 00:00:18.828
It compares amount, date, document number,

5
00:00:18.828 --> 00:00:23.373
description and counterparty while keeping every source visible.

6
00:00:24.885 --> 00:00:27.724
Strong matches move into the supported set.

7
00:00:27.724 --> 00:00:30.828
Ambiguous cases remain in the review queue with

8
00:00:30.828 --> 00:00:33.997
the reason and the specific document to inspect.

9
00:00:35.509 --> 00:00:40.408
The result is a workpaper that links every checked entry to its evidence,

10
00:00:40.408 --> 00:00:44.233
separates exceptions and preserves the verification path.

11
00:00:45.745 --> 00:00:49.200
From a sampled row to support the reviewer can follow.
